text: Sebastian Garro y Sidrac (14-15?) was a Basque nobleman, Viscount of Zolina, Lord of Rocafort and Sidrac. == Biography == Sebastian Garro was born in Navarra, son of a noble family. He was married to María de Gongora, daughter of an eminent Spanish family, descendants of the Marquises of Góngora. Garro was a possible descended of Pere Arnaut de Garro, a noble knight, who served in the court of Charles II of Navarre. == References == == External links == *navarchivo.com Category:16th-century deaths Category:Navarrese people Category:Basque history Category:Basque people
